{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Corellia_Vote",
  "title": "The Corellia Vote",
  "summary": "Before the New Republic's Ruling Council, chaired by Chief of State Leia Organa-Solo, Senator Tokoga presents the findings of his covert fact-finding mission to Corellia and argues for a decisive military operation to liberate the restive Imperial world. The hostile Security and Intelligence chair Krall Dar challenges his methods and warns of the catastrophic cost of failure, while the elderly Caamasi Justice chair counsels that the less-defended Gyndine would be the safer, more logical target. Tokoga counters that symbolic victories and humanitarian obligation outweigh raw caution, and a compromise of conditional aid is floated before the matter goes to a vote. The council splits evenly between conditional aid and a full liberation campaign, leaving the decision to Leia. She breaks the tie in favor of liberating Corellia, committing the Republic to the bold operation.",
